items.title: Taiwan to invest $250B in US semiconductor manufacturing
items.description: The U.S. struck a trade deal with Taiwan as the country looks to help boost domestic semiconductor manufacturing.

items.title: Iran’s internet shutdown is now one of its longest ever, as protests continue
items.description: Iran’s government-imposed internet shutdown enters its second week as authorities continue their violent crackdown on protesters.

items.title: The US imposes 25% tariff on Nvidia’s H200 AI chips headed to China
items.description: The Trump administration formalized its 25% cut of H200 chip sales in China with a tariff that applies to certain semiconductors.
